{"author":"Iso Tester","data":{"fields":{"description":"## Why\nWith many attestations every consumer must address a specific kind; today verify returns one verdict from one slot.\n## What\n`verify_signature(ticket_id, kind=...)` certifies a single kind; with no kind it returns a\n`{kind: verdict}` map over all present attestations. CLI: `--kind K` is the single-gate\nexit-code form (exit 0 iff certified); no `--kind` lists all (exit 0 iff all certified).\nSCOPE BOUNDARY: this story owns the `verify_signature` MCP tool + its result schema; the\n`attestations` field in the ticket-state MCP response is owned by ed26 (slap-slag-skull) —\ncoordinate on the shared attestation-record schema shape.\n## Scope\n`src/rebar/signing.py` (`verify_signature`, `verify_signature_cli`), `src/rebar/mcp_server.py`\n(verify tool only), `src/rebar/schemas/verify_signature_result.schema.json`.\n## Depends on\nRequires 114f (rusty-blend-panel) merged (reads `state[\"attestations\"]`).\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] `verify_signature(ticket_id, kind=...)` returns one verdict; no-kind returns `{kind: verdict}`.\n- [ ] CLI `--kind K` exit 0 iff that kind certified; no `--kind` lists all, exit 0 iff all certified.\n- [ ] MCP verify tool + result schema reflect the per-kind / map shapes.\n- [ ] Legacy single-signature ticket verifies under its derived kind."}},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"EDIT","timestamp":1782783760723416001,"uuid":"e763d4a9-6470-403d-8bbe-69aaf93b3fb9"}